{"type":"message","id":"029baeef","parentId":"5a034b8c","timestamp":"2026-04-02T17:54:26.981Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture of all the changes needed. Let me summarize the findings and prepare for the edits.\n\n## Summary of My Owned Files and Required Changes:\n\n### Files owned by Worker E (runtime integration):\n\n1. **ui/behaviors/midisynth.lua** (main file with most changes)\n   - `_rackNodeSpecs` → `_rackModuleSpecs` (many occurrences)\n   - `_dragPreviewNodes` → `_dragPreviewModules`\n   - `dragState.nodeId` → `dragState.moduleId`\n   - `dragState.baseNodes` → `dragState.baseModules`\n   - `__midiSynthDynamicNodeSpecs` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleSpecs`\n   - `__midiSynthRackNodeSpecs` → `__midiSynthRackModuleSpecs`\n   - `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo`\n   - `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` → `RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT`\n   - `ctx._rackState.nodes` → `ctx._rackState.modules`\n   - `from.nodeId` / `to.nodeId` → `from.moduleId` / `to.moduleId` (in connection context)\n   - `rack_node_shell` → `rack_module_shell`\n   - `RackNodeShell` → `RackModuleShell`\n   - API renames: `makeNodeSpec` → `makeRackModuleSpec`, `makeNodeInstance` → `makeRackModuleInstance`, `cloneNodes` → `cloneRackModules`, `nodeSpecById` → `rackModuleSpecById`\n\n2. **ui/behaviors/filter.lua**\n   - `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo`\n\n3. **ui/behaviors/eq.lua**\n   - `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo`\n\n4. **ui/behaviors/fx_slot.lua**\n   - `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo`\n\n5. **editor/runtime_state.lua**\n   - Connections: `from.nodeId` → `from.moduleId`, `to.nodeId` → `to.moduleId`\n   - `rackNodes` → `rackModules` (in serialized state)\n\n6. **lib/rack_audio_router.lua** - No changes needed, uses DSP node terminology correctly\n\n7. **lib/ui/rack_controller.lua** - The `nodeId` references here are for rail port binding (DSP node terminology), not rack module terminology. No changes needed based on the constraint to not rename DSP graph node terminology.\n\n8. **lib/ui/update_sync.lua** - Need to check the context of `nodeId` at line 600. The `ctx._rackState.viewMode` references are fine as they access state properties rather than module/node terminology. The `nodeId` on line 600 appears to reference a patchbay instance identifier, which would be part of the DSP graph node system and outside the scope of these renames.\n\n9. **dsp/main.lua** - No changes needed, this is DSP graph terminology (\"layer nodes\")\n\nThe critical constraint is to avoid renaming DSP graph node terminology—only rack-module-facing naming should change. `rackNodes` in the runtime state persists serialized rack module data, so it needs renaming. Connections reference rack module endpoints, so those get updated too.\n\nSeveral symbols need migration: `_rackNodeSpecs` becomes `_rackModuleSpecs`, `_dragPreviewNodes` becomes `_dragPreviewModules`, and drag state properties shift from `nodeId`/`baseNodes` to `moduleId`/`baseModules`. The global dynamic spec tables follow the same pattern, replacing \"Node\" with \"Module\" in their names.\n\n`RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` maps to `RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT`, and state references move from `.nodes` to `.modules`. Connection endpoints update from `from.nodeId`/`to.nodeId` to `from.moduleId`/`to.moduleId`. Component names shift from `rack_node_shell` to `rack_module_shell` and `RackNodeShell` to `RackModuleShell`. Runtime state connections need their endpoint identifiers migrated, and the `rackNodes` serialized field becomes `rackModules`. Now I'll run the edits.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Now I have the complete picture. Here's my summary:\n\n---\n\n## Worker E Summary: Runtime Integration Migration\n\n### Owned Files (9 total):\n1. `ui/behaviors/midisynth.lua` - Main runtime integration (heaviest changes)\n2. `ui/behaviors/filter.lua` - Dynamic module info lookup\n3. `ui/behaviors/eq.lua` - Dynamic module info lookup  \n4. `ui/behaviors/fx_slot.lua` - Dynamic module info lookup\n5. `editor/runtime_state.lua` - Serialized rack state with connections\n6. `lib/rack_audio_router.lua` - Audio routing (minimal/no changes - DSP graph terminology)\n7. `lib/ui/rack_controller.lua` - Rail port bindings (no changes - DSP node terminology)\n8. `lib/ui/update_sync.lua` - Patchbay instance tracking (no changes - DSP node terminology)\n9. `dsp/main.lua` - DSP integration (no changes - DSP graph terminology)\n\n### Required Renames in Owned Files:\n\n**midisynth.lua (primary):**\n- `_rackNodeSpecs` → `_rackModuleSpecs` (~18 hits)\n- `_dragPreviewNodes` → `_dragPreviewModules` (~17 hits)\n- `dragState.nodeId` → `dragState.moduleId` (~21 hits)\n- `dragState.baseNodes` → `dragState.baseModules` (~13 hits)\n- `__midiSynthDynamicNodeSpecs` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleSpecs` (~4 hits)\n- `__midiSynthRackNodeSpecs` → `__midiSynthRackModuleSpecs` (~4 hits)\n- `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo` (~8 hits)\n- `RACK_SHELL_LAYOUT` → `RACK_MODULE_SHELL_LAYOUT` (~18 hits)\n- `ctx._rackState.nodes` → `ctx._rackState.modules` (~30 hits)\n- `from.nodeId` / `to.nodeId` (connection context) → `from.moduleId` / `to.moduleId` (~6 hits)\n- `rack_node_shell` → `rack_module_shell` (1 hit)\n- `RackNodeShell` → `RackModuleShell` (2 hits)\n- API calls: `makeNodeSpec` → `makeRackModuleSpec`, `makeNodeInstance` → `makeRackModuleInstance`, `cloneNodes` → `cloneRackModules`, `nodeSpecById` → `rackModuleSpecById`\n\n**filter.lua, eq.lua, fx_slot.lua:**\n- `__midiSynthDynamicNodeInfo` → `__midiSynthDynamicModuleInfo` (1 hit each)\n\n**runtime_state.lua:**\n- `from.nodeId` / `to.nodeId` → `from.moduleId` / `to.moduleId` in connections (10 hits)\n- `rackNodes` → `rackModules` in serialized state (1 hit)\n\n### Hard Constraints:\n- ✅ Same repo, owned files ONLY\n- ✅ NO edits to shell/spec/core worker files\n- ✅ NO renaming of DSP graph node terminology (RuntimeNode, PrimitiveNode, layer nodes, etc.)\n- ✅ NO builds, cmake, ninja, standalone, VST\n- ✅ Verify with `luac -p` and `rg` only\n\n### External Dependencies on Other Workers:\n- `RackLayout.makeNodeSpec` → `RackLayout.makeRackModuleSpec` (Worker A)\n- `RackLayout.makeNodeInstance` → `RackLayout.makeRackModuleInstance` (Worker A)\n- `RackLayout.cloneNodes` → `RackLayout.cloneRackModules` (Worker A)\n- `MidiSynthRackSpecs.nodeSpecById()` → `MidiSynthRackSpecs.rackModuleSpecById()` (Worker B)\n- `components.rack_node_shell` → `components.rack_module_shell` (Worker D - file rename)\n\n### Risks/Hotspots:\n1. **midisynth.lua is large (~4600 lines)** - many occurrences, need careful line-by-line edits\n2. **Drag state shape changes** - `dragState.moduleId` and `dragState.baseModules` must stay consistent across the file\n3. **Connection serialization** - runtime_state.lua uses these shapes for persistence; changing endpoint field names affects saved projects\n4. **Global exports** - `_G.__midiSynthRackModuleSpecs` etc. may be consumed by other runtime scripts not in owned files\n\n### Validation Plan:\n1. `luac -p` each owned file after edits\n2. `rg` for old symbols in owned files to verify complete replacement\n3. Check for any stray `nodeId` usage that should remain (DSP graph context) vs. changed (rack module context)\n\n---\n\n**Ready to proceed. Send GO when you want me to execute the edits.**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding-plan","model":"kimi-for-coding","usage":{"input":1134,"output":1876,"cacheRead":46336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49346,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775152432352,"responseId":"msg_w1ItfJpw1auOPCzj9aTTe3NC"}}
